The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The use of memcomputing, a novel paradigm of computation, to solve these problems suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the scalability of memcomputing, which could be of interest to the subfield of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Emerging Technologies (cs.ET).
